    {
      "parameters": {
        "description": "Save information PERMANENTLY to the knowledge base. This is the ONLY way to persist data across conversations — session memory is temporary and will be lost.\n\n🚨 If a user provides ANY business info, preferences, contact details, or corrections → MUST use this tool. Session memory is NOT saving.\n\nPREREQUISITE: ALWAYS call \"Postgres PGVector RAG\" first to search for existing content before saving.\n\nWORKFLOW:\n1. Call \"Postgres PGVector RAG\" to search for existing data\n2. If exists → updating=true | If new → updating=false\n3. Call this tool with parameters below\n\nPARAMETERS:\n- query: Clear, structured text (e.g. \"Company: Acme Corp | Type: Property management | Location: Manchester\")\n- category: One of:\n  - \"user_preferences\" — Company info, contacts, business type, products, audience, brand voice, social profiles, and all other business facts or preferences\n  - \"result_of_analysis\" — Website analysis, competitor research, branding analysis outputs\n  - \"custom_instructions\" — User-defined rules for agent behaviour\n- source: Topic identifier (e.g. \"company_info\", \"contact_details\", \"products_services\", \"target_audience\", \"website_analysis\")\n- updating: true if replacing existing content, false if new\n\n🚫 NEVER claim data is \"saved\" or \"updated\" without calling this tool. Storing in session memory and saying \"Got it!\" is a failure.",
        "workflowId": {
          "__rl": true,
